        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 8 at 12:54PM CDT until May 8 at 1:15PM CDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 1252 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles southeast
of Beaver Dam, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Emergency management reported hail at 1237 PM CDT.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Beaver Dam, Rosine, Horton, Mount Pleasant, Windy Hill, Select, Flint
Springs, Rob Roy, Sandefur Crossing, and Cromwell.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
